HB 4138-A11
(LC 30)
2/26/26 (JLM/ps)
Requested by Representative CHAICHI
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
A-ENGROSSED HOUSE BILL 4138
1 On page 6 of the printed A-engrossed bill, delete lines 8 through 17 and
2 insert:
3 “SECTION 10. (1) Prior to providing assistance or cooperating with,
4 or allowing time, money, facilities, property, equipment, personnel or
5 other resources to be used to assist, cooperate with or facilitate, an
6 operation executed in whole or in part by a federal law enforcement
7 agency or a law enforcement agency of another state, a state or local
8 law enforcement agency or other public body, or an employee or agent
9 of a state or local law enforcement agency or other public body, may
10 obtain from the federal or out-of-state law enforcement agency an
11 attestation, made under penalty of perjury, stating that the request
12 does not relate to an operation or other activity prohibited by section
13 8 of this 2026 Act or a policy adopted pursuant to section 9 of this 2026
14 Act.
15 “(2) Notwithstanding section 8 of this 2026 Act or any policy adopted
16 pursuant to section 9 of this 2026 Act, a state or local law enforcement
17 agency or other public body, or an employee or agent of a state or
18 local law enforcement agency or other public body, that provides any
19 assistance or cooperation to a federal law enforcement agency or law
20 enforcement agency of another state, does not violate section 8 of this
21 2026 Act, or any policy established under section 9 of this 2026 Act, if

1 the assistance or cooperation is provided after receiving an attestation
2 described in subsection (1) of this section.
3 “(3) Nothing in this section requires a state or local law enforce-
4 ment agency or other public body, or an employee or agent of a state
5 or local law enforcement agency or other public body, to obtain the
6 attestation described in subsection (1) of this section prior to, during
7 or after providing any assistance to or cooperating with a federal law
8 enforcement agency or a law enforcement agency of another state.”.
